      "This dashboard was built to visualize cryptocurrency data fetched from the CoinGecko API. The aim was to create a user-friendly interface for tracking and analyzing crypto market information. Key features include sortable tables displaying real-time data such as price, market capitalization, and trading volume for various cryptocurrencies. Additionally, the dashboard incorporates charts to illustrate historical price trends. This project demonstrates my skills in working with APIs, data visualization libraries (potentially like Chart.js or similar), data handling, and front-end development to present complex information in an accessible and informative way.",
    image: cryptoDashboardImage,
    link: "https://crypto-new-dashboard.vercel.app/",
    repoLink: "https://github.com/YPPupo/crypto-new-dashboard.git",
    tags: ["React", "Next js", "API", "Chart.js", "Vercel"],
    featured: false,
    isPrivated: false,
  },
  {
    title: "Audio Transcriptions",
    description:
      "An audio-to-text transcription application powered by OpenAI's Whisper API. This tool allows users to upload audio files and receive accurate text transcriptions. The application requires a valid OpenAI API key for processing, which is used client-side for direct API communication and is never stored. The project demonstrates secure API key handling, file processing, and real-time transcription capabilities. Built with modern web technologies, it showcases my ability to integrate with AI services while maintaining user privacy and data security.",
    image: audioTranscriptionsImage,
    link: "https://yppupo.github.io/audio-transcriptions/",
    repoLink: "https://github.com/YPPupo/audio-transcriptions.git",
    tags: ["React", "Vite", "Github Pages"],
    featured: false,
    isPrivated: false,
  },
  {
    title: "FM Devfinder",
    description:
      "This project is a solution to the GitHub User Finder challenge from Frontend Mentor. It demonstrates my ability to interact with external APIs and dynamically display data. Users can input a GitHub username, and the application fetches and presents relevant profile information using the GitHub API. This includes the user's avatar, bio, follower/following counts, public repositories, and more. The project highlights my proficiency in API integration, asynchronous JavaScript, DOM manipulation, and responsive design principles.",
    image: devfinderImage,
    link: "https://fm-devfinder.vercel.app/",
    repoLink: "https://github.com/YPPupo/fm-devfinder.git",
    tags: ["React", "Next js", "API", "Vercel"],
    featured: false,
    isPrivated: false,
  },
  {
    title: "Testing Calculator",
    description:
      "A simple calculator application designed to demonstrate comprehensive testing practices. This project showcases my expertise in writing and implementing various types of tests, including unit tests, integration tests, and end-to-end (e2e) tests. The calculator performs basic arithmetic operations while serving as a practical example of test-driven development (TDD) principles. The project highlights my ability to ensure code reliability, maintainability, and robustness through thorough testing methodologies in a modern JavaScript/TypeScript environment.",
